    "created_at": "2015-09-21T23:39:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-21T23:40:16Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've been wanting to revive my super-flexible FNA controls setup project for a while now, which I was designing to handle stuff just like that. I got the core key/button/etc logic working, but I never got around to analog input (thumbsticks, mouse movement, sliders, accelerometers) and differentiating between clicks and drags (handling C&C style \"orders/selection vs box selection\" and \"deselection vs mouse scrolling\" were explicit design goals) or proper (de)serialization. After I dust the bitrot off it, add mouse support, add defaults/profile support (so you can offer defaults of Right-Click Orders and Left-Click Orders), and genericize it so it doesn't rely on any FNA-specific stuff, I'll look into doing that. (This is how I enjoy spending my free time.)\n\nAs a stopgap, I'd recommend right-click orders keeping \"scroll map\" on middle mouse for those used to the ORA default controls, and hardcoding left-click orders to have \"scroll map\" on right-mouse for those used to the Westwood default controls.\n"
  },
