    "created_at": "2016-02-01T15:08:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-01T15:39:34Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Now that the joystick option for Mouse 2 is up and running, are there any incentive to work on rebinding the drag-scroll button (standard) from Mouse 3 to Mouse 2? Using Mouse 3 button for drag-scrolling is still awkward. I'm hoping the solution for the joystick option can spill over to this issue.\n\nI understand the joystick was added in the prospect of TS, RA2. I think it's important to note that since the originals had way lower resolutions, the joystick was a more effective means to scroll over big distances. On OpenRA, the drag-scroll is vastly superior for controlling the camera, especially on 720p and up. Together with hotkey binded double-pixeling, most maps can be camera dragged to a pinpoint location in a split second. In the end it might just be a personal preference but I hope there's enough interest to complete this ticket.\n"
